iated with deconstruction, among them Jacques Derrida, Judith Butler, and Avital Ronnel. Ranging across a wide field, from the ethics of reading to the rhetoric of performance, the contributors offer provocative insights into a new sense of the political. The America of the volume's title turns out to be the place where the politics and poetics of responsibility meet. It is also the place where we confront the tension between difference and profound otherness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Essays.2bisacsh  aAmerican.  aThis.  aWhat.  aaddress.  aassociated.  abrings.  aculture.  adeconstruction.  adeconstructive.  aimpact.  aimportant.  aitself.  amost.  apeculiarly.  aquestions.  aread.  asome.  athese.  athinkers.  atogether.  avolume.  awith.1 aAttridge, Derek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaujour, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButler, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChase, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuller, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDerrida, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDodge, H. R., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aEisenman, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGasché, Rodolphe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaverkamp, Anselm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamuf, Peggy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc